Class MultilineMacro

java.lang.Object
org.variantsync.diffdetective.diff.difftree.parse.MultilineMacro
public class MultilineMacro extends Object
Represents a multiline macro definition in a diff during parsing of a text-based diff.

  • Constructor Details

    • MultilineMacro

      public MultilineMacro​(String line, DiffType diffType, DiffLineNumber startLine, DiffNode beforeParent, DiffNode afterParent)
      Create the definition of a multiline macro from the given values.
      Parameters:
      line - The corresponding line in the diff.
      diffType - The diff type of this multiline macro.
      startLine - The line number at which the definition of this macro began.
      beforeParent - The parent of this macro before the edit.
      afterParent - The parent of this macro after the edit.

    • toDiffNode

      public DiffNode toDiffNode​(DiffNodeParser nodeParser) throws IllFormedAnnotationException
      Parses this multiline macro definition in a DiffNode.
      Parameters:
      nodeParser - This parse is used to create the DiffNode after all lines of this multiline macro are joined to a single line.
      Returns:
      A DiffNode representing this multiline macro.
      Throws:
      IllFormedAnnotationException - when DiffNodeParser.fromDiffLine(String) fails.
